13-year-old Eilon has spent all his life living in the shadow of rockets fired from #Gaza into his hometown of Sderot in Southern Israel. During last year's war he and his younger sister Agam weren't allowed to be more than 14 seconds away from a bombproof room. 

Their story features in "Children of the Gaza War" a documentary in which the BBC's Chief international correspondent Lyse Doucet follows the lives of children on both sides of the conflict.

12-year-old Samar returns to #Gaza to see the building where her family used to live before it was destroyed by an Israeli strike during last summer's war. 

This is the first of two videos featured in "Children of the Gaza War" a documentary from our Chief international correspondent Lyse Doucet. Later we'll focus on the story of Eilon, a child from Sderot in Southern Israel.
